What a group of gems 💎 @dallyssblonde @dopplerdrew @brittanyroseblog @kateenloe @stephaniecamillee @annacdavis_ @emmacastelan @averyabi @raefranko - but missing @kenrightphotography, @mctinez817, and of course @laurenseegers 

Add it to the love list ✨💕

LOVE LIST HAS AN HQ 🎉🥂✨

It’s official, we bought an office and Love List finally has a home in Dallas ✨💕 Now begins the fun part of 🎨 making it “on brand”! COLOR, here we come 🥰

This is information no one cares about BUT I miss posting for fun on this account. I devote so much time to Love List that I forget - hey I genuinely ✨love✨ documenting adventures. 

So alas, @dopplerdrew and I are on day two of a Miami, Key West, Fort Lauderdale adventure and I want to share it!

Social media is a highlight reel - and this is a high highlight. 

Not pictured - This was a really long, challenging work trip spanning 5 days and three cities. My feet hurt, I’m worn out mentally and physically. I’m also very cold sitting outside at the moment 😂

But my goodness, the trip is concluding with this view and a phenomenal hazy IPA. I wouldn’t trade this job, this opportunity for anything in the world.

@addittothelovelist ✨💕

Confession: I didn’t think I’d have fun at Pete’s. I was so wrong. 
They have a carajillo on the menu with fat ice and uber-talented performers on the pianos, drums, electric guitar and vocals. Sometimes all at once. I’m still processing. More to come…huge thanks to @fortworthlovelist for bringing us along for the wildest ride in the *front row.*

#therapydupe #dupes #singloud #fortworth #fortworthtx #fortworthbars #petespianobar

✨WHEN YOUR HOBBY BECOMES YOUR FULL-TIME JOB ✨

I’ve been talking to a few friends who are all in the social media industry about hobbies - most recently as of today, @StreetsBeatsEats. 

Even though it has been three years, I don’t think I ever really processed that my favorite hobby - @DallasLoveList- is now classified as “work”. I’m so thankful for my job, I truly would not trade it for any other job on the planet, but posting does feel like work in the long run. 

But I then remembered this feed with cobwebs on it. So I’m going to try and post every day for 30 days to try and kickstart me back into my old “hobby” ways, and find a little joy in social media along the way. 

So here is day 1 of 30. I opened a new cross stitch my mom @AnnCaudleVB sent me, I got a 60 minute head scratch with @Streetsbeatseats, had a fabulous Caesar wrap from @shadysburgersrichardson , had a guest doggo at the house thanks to @TheCoziestGal_, then finished with emails and one of my favorite beers from @PantherIslandbrewing. 

See you tomorrow for day 2 (hint, we are going to the casino….)

Day 2 of posting for 30 days because I genuinely love social media. We had a @dallaslovelist campaign with the @dallascowboys and then visited our long term, amazing partner @choctawcasinos for the @marenmorris concert! 

I truly love @choctawcasinos, it’s my favorite quick road trip! If you need me the rest of the night I’ll be flipping 21 ♥️♠️

Not a bad way to spend a Saturday ✨💕

DALLAS LOVE LIST JUST HIT 400k !!!! And it just so happens that today, June 2nd, is also the 7 year anniversary/birthday of Dallas Love List, and today is also the 17th anniversary since I lost my Dad. How do these all happen at the same time?? 

I’m so proud of our team of SIXTEEN (!!) incredible humans who shows up with creativity and enthusiasm every single day. 

Coolest thing on the planet right now.
Happy Freaking Birthday to the man, the myth, the miller lite legend @dopplerdrew. I spend every waking second with you so it’s a damn good thing I love you so freaking much.

What an incredible long weekend in the most beautiful place Isla Holbox 🏝️ celebrating @haydenwayne32. 

✨@lilyktsmith, you were the ultimate hostess and we made some incredible new friends. 

✨🍹Really struggled to choose 10 pics but in the end the 10th frame was a non-negotiable!

It’s the end of an era, @BrittanyRoseBlog x Love List. I can’t wait to see what you accomplish from here but damn imma miss you. Love you friend, there simply is no Love List without BRB. 

If you need me for the next few days, I’ll be in the corner with tissues.

My favorite day of the year - @StateFairofTx opening day. ✨2020 was my first year doing @dallaslovelist full time and my bestie @susiedrinksdallas was kind enough to go with me
✨2021 was our first time as a team at the fair of 4
✨2022 we had a team of 10 
✨2023 we are rolling 21 deep… totally unreal 

I am so incredibly thankful to this squad pictured above. Hard workers, hustlers and most importantly creative AF! 

Add it to the love list ✨💕
ADD THE TEXAS RANGERS TO THE LOVE LIST
File this one under top ten days as a sports fan named Sarah Mize! Cover is a photo with the MVP himself @coreyseager5. The 4th slide is my new favorite video of all time
And just like that, it’s the holiday season at the Mize’s 🎄🎅

I GOT A HOLE IN ONE OH MY GOD!!!! ⛳️

We just joined @miravistacountryclub on Friday (so pumped for that) and today was very first intro round that they were kind enough to setup as new members. So first time ever playing this course, and it was cold so I clubbed up on number 12 and flushed a 5 iron from 149 yards and it landed right of the pin into the dang hole!! You could have heard a pin drop between me and @dopplerdrew as we saw the ball disappear.

We raced to the green and there was a guy working on the fence in the yard behind and we were like DID THAT GO IN??? And he smile and nodded and I’ll never get over this.

I’ve been playing since I was a little kid and this is my very first time even flirting with a hole out, let alone a hole in one. Nothing can take me off this high today. Having a day ⛳️ 

So yes I should like being a member at @miravistacountryclub ✨
Christmas at the beach with @anncaudlevb ✨💕

I haven’t told anyone this but spending New Years in Key West one year apart - ✨down 55 pounds✨ and so proud of myself 💖🪩 

Swipe for last year in Key West vs this year and feeling 💯
